+# Step-6 Is Well Posed Because The Post-Repair Shortlist Freezes To Two Repaired Objects
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` chain-step verdict with `INFERRED` shortlist synthesis
+
+The completed Step-5 repair pass leaves the exact-NS near-closure branch with
+one final post-repair shortlist on the already frozen packet ledger.
+
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure` survives as a repaired exact object on the same
+canonical packet sheet, with the repaired defect sheet
+`(1/4, 49/256)`
+and the friendly stress witness
+`F_SL(1/16)`
+carried forward to the downstream freeze.
+
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` survives as a repaired exact object on
+the same frozen interaction currency and spectator partition, with the
+repaired classwise budget sheet
+`(1/4, 1/12, 1/12, 1/16, 1/24)`
+and the friendly stress set
+`F_SS(1/12)`
+plus
+`F_SL(1/16)`
+carried forward to the downstream freeze.
+
+`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` does not remain on that shortlist.
+Its early split stays exact only as a narrow admission filter, while its late
+split is not well-defined on the frozen event language.
+So the behavioral route is fully discarded rather than left as shortlist
+baggage.
+
+Chain Step 6 is therefore well posed:
+freeze those two repaired objects on the same ledger, keep hostile
+`F_DT(delta, eta)` as the reference negative comparator, and do not stop the
+branch at Step 5 merely because the itinerary route collapsed.
+
+Filed from:
